Very interesting book. Would not suggest it to someone inquiring into Orthodoxy over something like Fr. Seraphim Rose's books, but a good read nonetheless. Mother Alexandra is the Romanian princess who was exiled and died in the USA. She's a great granddaughter of Queen Victoria.

I remember I had a wonderful kitchen Chef mutual (maybe he's still around?) who always got very angry when someone mentioned Michelin star restaurants because he believed the Michelin star system was corrupt/a scam. Insanely funny concept. I love cuisine and the people behind it.

I appreciate that there are people like this in the world. It's nice when you're walking to see a group of normies in the distance having fun together laughing etc. Not the type of life for us and not who we are, but it's nice that they exist out there.

Like he used to say if a place had a Michelin star the food must probably be mediocre there and was annoyed that customers were getting tricked by it, etc. Maybe "Bridgestone" or "Continental" should start a rival, more rigorous restaurant star rating system.

One absolutely insane little detail is that when Sir Keir Starmer went to Ukraine to sign the UK deal for some incomprehensible reason he decided to also dress up as Zelensky in a t-shirt (as a mutual framed it, "cosplaying Zelensky").

He arrived dressed in a real suit and specifically changed into the Zelensky cosplay t-shirt for this video then later changed back into the suit. The English mind. Some insufferable semiotics memes about simulacra and representation to be made here by those into that stuff.
